benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/tags - Remove tags from invoice item

covered: Valid Deletion: TC01 covers successful removal of all tags (204) and empty body.
Selective Deletion: TC02 covers removing a subset via tagDef and verifies only specified tags are removed.
Header/Reason/Comment: TC03 verifies optional headers handling.
No Tags Present: TC04 ensures idempotent behavior when no tags exist.
TagDef Edge Cases: TC05 handles tag IDs not present on item; TC06 handles empty tagDef; TC07 handles extra query params.
Non-existent/Invalid IDs: TC08 (non-existent item), TC09 (invalid UUID format).
Missing Header/Auth: TC10 (missing header) and TC11 (invalid token).
Service Availability: TC12 (service unavailable) and TC19 (dependent service unavailable).
Malformed inputs: TC13 (malformed tagDef), TC15 (malicious payload in headers), TC16 (partial tagDef), TC20 (accessibility considerations).
Large tagDef and limits: TC14 tests very large tagDef and behavior based on system limits.
Concurrency/Performance: TC17 (high concurrency) and TC18 (special-character in comment for regression).
Regression/Integration: TC18 and TC19 cover historical/regression and integration considerations.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for large datasets or listing results with pagination semantics.
Caching Behavior: No tests validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or caching behavior for this endpoint.
Explicit Authorization Scenarios: While TC11 covers invalid token, there is no explicit test for unauthorized (e.g., 401) vs forbidden (403) under valid token presence/absence scenarios beyond that.
Soft Delete Semantics: No explicit test confirming whether deletions are soft (flag) vs hard delete for tags themselves.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate burst or throttling behavior for multiple rapid DELETE requests.
Detailed 207/204 distinction for integration fault: TC19 mentions 204 or 207 depending on design but no deeper coverage of partial failures nor exact error payloads in mixed-integrations.
Data integrity under concurrency: While TC17 exists, there is no scenario explicitly asserting race-condition avoidance under concurrent updates to the same invoice item tags.
Edge-case header combinations: TC03/TC15 cover headers broadly but additional negative tests for combinations (e.g., valid header with invalid reason/comment) could be explored.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination behavior when listing or retrieving large tag sets to simulate and validate proper pagination semantics for tag definitions, if applicable to the API design.
Add caching tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control headers on DELETE responses and any conditional requests behavior.
Introduce explicit unauthorized/forbidden scenarios beyond token validity, e.g., missing permissions leading to 403, to align with authorization guidelines.
Add soft-delete semantics verification if the system supports non-destructive deletions (e.g., marking, not removing data), and validate recovery paths if applicable.
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure system resilience under burst DELETE requests.
Expand concurrency tests to explicitly validate race conditions when multiple clients attempt to delete tags on the same item simultaneously, including data integrity checks.
Enhance TC19 with more granular outcomes for partial failures across integrations (audit/logging, etc.) and verify exact response body shapes for 204 vs 207 scenarios.
Include more focused accessibility tests tied to error message readability and documentation accessibility checks (TC20) with screen-reader-friendly payloads and structures.
